quran[27]{c,v,t,f}:
37,25,"How is it that you are not helping one another?"
37,26,"Indeed, today they are surrendering themselves completely.” {1}",footnotes:1:The first sentence will be addressed to the culprits
37,27,"They will then turn towards each other (and start wrangling)."
37,28,"(The followers will say to their leaders): “You used to come to us from the right hand.” {1}",footnotes:1:The word yameen in Arabic is used for several meanings. It may mean use of the force
37,29,"They will say: “Nay, you yourselves were not the ones who would believe."
37,30,"We had no power over you. You were a rebellious people,"
37,31,"and so we became deserving of the Word of our Lord that we shall be made to suffer chastisement."
37,32,"So we led you astray; we ourselves were strayed.” {1}",footnotes:1:For explanation see ( E.Ns 51
37,33,"On that Day, they will all share the chastisement. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
37,34,"Thus do We treat the culprits."
37,35,"Whenever it was said to them: “There is no true deity apart from Allah,” they waxed proud"
37,36,"and said: “Shall we forsake our deities for the sake of a distracted poet?”"
37,37,"(They say so although) he brought the Truth and confirmed the veracity of the Messengers. {1}",footnotes:1:Confirmation of the Messengers has three meanings and all the three are implied here.
37,38,"(They will be told): “You shall taste the grievous chastisement."
37,39,"You will only be recompensed according to your deeds.”"
37,40,"But Allah's chosen servants (shall be spared this woeful end)."
37,41,"For them awaits a known provision, {1}",footnotes:1:“A provision
37,42,"a variety of delicious fruits; and they shall be honoured {1}",footnotes:1:In this there is also a subtle allusion to the fact that
37,43,"in the Gardens of Bliss."
37,44,"They will be seated upon couches set face to face;"
37,45,"a cup filled with wine {1} from its springs, {2} will be passed around to them; {3}",footnotes:1:Here the word kaas (cup) only has been used and there is no mention of the wine. But in Arabic the use of kass always implies wine. The cup which contains milk or water
37,46,"white, sparkling (wine), a delight to the drinkers."
37,47,"There will neither be any harm in it for their body nor will it intoxicate their mind. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
37,48,"Theirs shall be wide-eyed maidens {1} with bashful, restrained glances, {2}",footnotes:1:“Restraining their looks”: Restraining their looks from everyone except their husbands.|180717:Probably
37,49,"so delicate as the hidden peel under an egg's shell. {1}",footnotes:1:The words of the text actually mean this: As if they were the hidden or well preserved eggs. The commentators have given different interpretations of these words
37,50,"Then some of them will turn to others, and will ask each other."
37,51,"One of them will say: “I had a companion in the world"
